  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to improve care practice related to gastrostomy management. This a
      before-after study, aimed at evaluating knowledge of care givers, families and patients about
      gastrostomy management. The intervention includes 1) A training in a care protocol for
      hospital care givers, and 2) A booklet for patients, families, and outpatient care givers.
      The evaluation criterion is a questionnaire to assess knowledge of hospital care givers,
      patients, families, and outpatient care givers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
